<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b50a0a5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s635"><num value="635">§ 635.</num><heading> Coast Guard anchorages</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may perform dredging at Federal expense within and adjacent to anchorages established by the Coast Guard pursuant to existing authorities.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b50a0a6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/260/dAA/tI/s106">Pub. L. 116–260, div. AA, title I, § 106</ref>, <date date="2020-12-27">Dec. 27, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/2623">134 Stat. 2623</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6b50a0a7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id6b50a0a8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="miscellaneous" id="id6b50a0a9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">“Secretary” Defined</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Secretary means the Secretary of the Army, see <ref href="/us/pl/116/260/dAA/s2">section 2 of div. AA of Pub. L. 116–260</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s2201">section 2201 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
